<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17431012-13">
               <interp inst="t17431012-13" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17431012-13" type="year" value="1743"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17431012-13" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17431012"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17431012-13" type="date" value="17431012"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17431012-13-off53-c122" targOrder="Y" targets="t17431012-13-defend146 t17431012-13-off53 t17431012-13-verdict55"></join>
         
               <p>474. 
               
                  <persName id="t17431012-13-defend146" type="defendantName">
                     Thomas 
                     Gardner 
                  <interp inst="t17431012-13-defend146" type="surname" value="Gardner"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-defend146" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-defend146" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17431012-13-off53" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-off53" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-off53" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a Cloth Coat, value 10 s. the Goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17431012-13-victim148" type="victimName">
                           John 
                           Wood 
                        <interp inst="t17431012-13-victim148" type="surname" value="Wood"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17431012-13-victim148" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17431012-13-victim148" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                      
                  ; and a Brass Snuff-box
            </rs>, the Goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t17431012-13-victim150" type="victimName">
                     George 
                     Gray 
                  <interp inst="t17431012-13-victim150" type="surname" value="Gray"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-victim150" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-victim150" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17431012-13-cd54" type="crimeDate">Octob. 4</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17431012-13-off53 t17431012-13-cd54"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17431012-13-person151">
                  Thomas 
                  Averil 
               <interp inst="t17431012-13-person151" type="surname" value="Averil"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-person151" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-person151" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . There was a Coat brought to 
               <persName id="t17431012-13-person152">
                  George 
                  Gray 
               <interp inst="t17431012-13-person152" type="surname" value="Gray"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-person152" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-person152" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             to mend, the Prisoner had been at the Globe Alehouse in Crutebed-Fryars that Morning; I believe an Hour; Wood said, he believed the Man had stole his coat; I pursued the Prisoner, and<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="174310120009"></xptr> took him at the Navy Office Back-Gate, with the Coat just by him, about nine o'Clock, and brought him back; he was stooping down, and seemed to shuffle something.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17431012-13-person153">
                  George 
                  Gray 
               <interp inst="t17431012-13-person153" type="surname" value="Gray"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-person153" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-person153" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I had this Coat to mend; I left it in my Stall but a little while, and when I came to look for it, it was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17431012-13-person154">
                  John 
                  Lock 
               <interp inst="t17431012-13-person154" type="surname" value="Lock"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-person154" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-person154" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I found the Coat at the Prisoner's Feet, at the Navy-Office. <rs id="t17431012-13-verdict55" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-verdict55" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17431012-13-punish56" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17431012-13-punish56" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17431012-13-defend146 t17431012-13-punish56"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
